            <title>[MAHOUT-979] RowSimilarityJob should be able to infer the number of columns from the input matrix if not specified </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-979</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Presently RowSimilarityJob expects to be provided the &apos;numberOfColumns&apos; (-r) by the user and this is not an optional argument. If this is not specified explicitly RowSimilarityJob should be able to get the number of columns by the vector size. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
